      "content": "i see what you mean about the vibe. but i'm curious about the word choice specifically. when you say things like \"vibrant\" or \"eclectic\" or \"diverse\" in options B and C, do you feel like those descriptors inherently lower the perceived prestige of a neighborhood compared to more traditional descriptors? like, is there a reason why \"diversity\" or \"cultural fusion\" is being framed as less \"refined\" than \"colonial architecture\" or \"tradition\"?",
